text: Cetonana is a genus of araneomorph spiders in the family Trachelidae, first described by Embrik Strand in 1929. ==Species== it contains five species: *Cetonana laticeps (Canestrini, 1868) — Europe, Russia (Caucasus) *Cetonana lineolata (Mello-Leitão, 1941) — Brazil *Cetonana petrunkevitchi Mello-Leitão, 1945 — Brazil *Cetonana setosa (Simon, 1897) — Brazil *Cetonana shaanxiensis Jin, Yin & Zhang, 2017 — China ==References== ==External links== Category:Araneomorphae genera Category:Trachelidae
title: Cetonana
